longBusinessSummary: Afcons Infrastructure Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in infrastructure, engineering, and construction business. The company undertakes construction contracting of buildings, roads, sewage, railway lines, utility projects, bridges, dams, ports, marine works, highways, metro works, power houses, tunnels, oil and gas facilities, LNG tanks, and other general civil engineering projects in India, Bangladesh, the Maldives, Africa, and the Middle East countries. It is also involved in the construction, fabrication, and erection of overhead transmission line systems; production and erection of electrical switching plants, distribution boards, control panels, and active corrosion protection systems, as well as related maintenance solutions; and conclusion and execution of civil work, steel construction, road processing, and tunnel treatment projects. In addition, the company provides engineering, design, and consultancy services, including engineering, procurement, and construction; contract drilling, production, offshore construction, dredging, and marine services for offshore oil industries; and piling and foundation contracting, and prestressed concrete contracting services. Further, it engages in the investment and financial activities; and provision of internal water transport of goods, as well as road transportation activities. The company was formerly known as Asia Foundations and Constructions Limited and changed its name to Afcons Infrastructure Limited in August 1996. Afcons Infrastructure Limited was founded in 1959 and is based in Mumbai, India. Afcons Infrastructure Limited operates as a subsidiary of Goswami Infratech Private Limited.
